==English==
===Etymology===
It is widely accepted that '''meh''' was brought into the limelight by the television show ''[[w:The Simpsons|The Simpsons]]'', specifically in the episode titled ''"Hungry Hungry Homer"'' (Season 12, Episode 15,)<br><br>
:Homer: Kids... how would you... like to go to... Blocko Land??<br>
:Lisa/Bart: Meh.<br>
:Homer: But ... the TV gave me the impression that ...<br>
:Bart: We said "meh".<br>
:Lisa: M-e-h. Meh.

===Interjection===
'''meh'''

# An interjection expressing [[indifference]], [[apathy]], or "[[I don't know]]"; the verbal equivalent of a shrug of the shoulders
#: ''"What do you want for dinner?" &mdash; "Meh. I’m not really hungry."''
#: ''"That film was awesome!" &mdash; "Meh. I’ve seen better.
#: ''"How are you feeling today?" &mdash; "Meh...."

